                    <msContents>
                        <summary>Twenty-seven folios, primarily illustrated, detached from a
                            mid-sixteenth century Safavid manuscript of the <title>Akhlāq-i
                                Muḥsinī</title> (Morals of the Beneficent). A highly influential and
                            widel-read text on ethics, it contains forty chapters on different moral
                            topics. While author <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc"
                                key="person_90770167">Vāʿiẓ Kāshifī Sabzivārī (d. ca.
                                1504)</persName> dedicated it to Timurid ruler Sulṭān Ḥusayn Bayqarā
                            (b. 1438, r. 1469–1506), he composed it for the ruler's son, <persName>
                                Abū al-Muḥsin Mīrzā (d. 1507)</persName>. These detached folios
                            feature the original lavishly illuiminated opening and depictions
                            executed by the same artist.</summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="Hart_19223-item1" n="1">
                            <title key="work_219" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Akhlāq-i Muḥsinī</title>
                            <title key="work_219" xml:lang="fa">اخلاق محسنی</title>
                            <title key="work_219" type="desc">Morals of the Beneficent</title>
                            <author key="person_90770167" ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/90770167/">
                                <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Vāʿiẓ Kāshifī Sabzivārī, Kamāl
                                    al-Dīn Ḥusayn bin ʿAlī Bayhaqī, d. ca. 1504</persName>; <lb/>
                                <persName xml:lang="fa">واعظ کاشفی سبزواری، کمال‌الدین حسین بن علی
                                    بیهقی (د: ۹۱۰ ق/۱۵۰۴م)‏</persName>
                            </author>
                            <incipit xml:lang="fa"> حضرت پادشاه علی الاطلاق عزت كلمته و جلت عظمته
                                منشور دولت سلطان المرسلين و متمم اخلاق المحسنين محمد النبي الامي الا
                                مين را صلوات الله  و سلامه علیه و اله اجمعین بطغرای غرای
                                «[وَ]إِنَّكَ لَعَلى خُلُقٍ عَظِيمٍ» مرتفع و مزین کردانید زیرا که جسن
                                خلق نوریست از انوار حکمت آلهی… </incipit>

                            <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                            <note>For another folio that sold at auction, see Sotheby's London
                                    (<date>26 April 2023</date>), lot 38.</note>
                        </msItem>

                    </msContents>

